<li data-qa="ContentSchemaRender-defaultRenderMapFunctions-Component-3" class="css-1mniedq eq9i94311">Web3 is being held up as a win for democracy, and a growing collection of banned Chinese books shared via IPFS illustrates the challenges for censors</li>
</ul></div></div><div data-qa="GenericArticle-Sponsor" class="css-kerpr7 eg5341w18"></div><div data-qa="GenericArticle-Follow" class="css-1ltyhhv eg5341w17"><div class=" e1oct4f910 css-3yvbpc efd77580" data-qa="ArticleTopicFollowWidget-Container"><a target="_self" class="efd77584 e15alpai0 css-e3lja1 ef1hf1w0" href="/topics/censorship" data-qa="BaseLink-renderAnchor-StyledAnchor">Censorship</a><div data-qa="ArticleTopicFollowWidget-Divider" class="css-1vto17z efd77583"></div><div class="efd77582 css-18r8al4 egvgbya0" data-qa="FollowButton-ChildrenContainer"><button class="css-1mm5saa eklawst0" data-qa="follow-button">+ FOLLOW</button></div></div></div><div data-qa="GenericArticle-Author" class="css-16mapcj eg5341w16"><div class=" e1oct4f923 css-8vzp8b e4nambs3" data-qa="ArticleAuthorBlock-ArticleAuthorBlockContainer"><div data-qa="ArticleAuthorBlock-AvatarContainer" class="css-k3lus2 e4nambs6"><figure class="e4nambs7 css-1kkqnnx eipyg200" data-qa="AuthorAvatar-Figure"><a target="_self" class="eipyg201 css-127t9hs ef1hf1w0" href="/author/matt-haldane" data-qa="BaseLink-renderAnchor-StyledAnchor"><img alt="Matt Haldane" data-qa="BaseImage-handleRenderImage-StyledImage" class="eipyg203 css-1jh68lp em4672x0" loading="lazy" src="https://img.i-scmp.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=contain,width=60,format=auto/sites/default/files/styles/300x300/public/d8/images/author/pic/2019/06/06/matt_haldane_.jpg?itok=ysJ1BjsT"/></a></figure></div><div data-qa="ArticleAuthorBlock-InformationContainer" class="css-1yezj9g e4nambs5"><div data-qa="AuthorHeaderBar-StyledDiv" class="css-1dov09q eztcpbh0"></div><div data-qa="AuthorNames-AuthorNamesContainer" class="e4nambs0 css-1cwu7fy ezwgrp93"><a target="_self" class="e1yv8vq90 css-uvyeg2 ef1hf1w0" href="/author/matt-haldane" data-qa="BaseLink-renderAnchor-StyledAnchor">Matt Haldane</a><div class="e4nambs1 css-26nl1v egvgbya0" data-qa="FollowButton-ChildrenContainer"><button class="css-22u25n eklawst0" data-qa="follow-button">+ FOLLOW</button></div></div><div data-qa="ArticleAuthorBlock-ArticleDateAndLabelContainer" class="css-164bi9e e4nambs4"><div data-qa="DefaultArticleDate-StyledDiv" class="css-1c38abh e1lqw8if2"><div data-qa="DefaultArticleDate-PublishedDateContainer" class="css-ucvzz7 e1lqw8if1"><time dateTime="2022-04-16T02:30:24.000Z" data-qa="DefaultArticleDate-time">Published: <!-- -->10:30am, 16 Apr 2022</time></div></div><div class="e4nambs2 css-clmohc eogvy9v2" data-qa="ArticleTrustLabel-Container"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" data-qa="ArticleTrustLabel-StyledTrustLogo" class="css-xbpgdl eogvy9v1"><path d="M16.8 0C18.56 0 20 1.44 20 3.2v13.6c0 1.76-1.44 3.2-3.2 3.2H3.2A3.21 3.21 0 0 1 0 16.8V3.2C0 1.44 1.44 0 3.2 0h13.6zm0 1.2H3.2c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v13.6c0 1.1.9 2 2 2h13.6c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2V3.2c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2zm-1 3.38c.08 0 .14.06.14.14V8.2c0 .08-.06.14-.14.14h-3.54c-.08 0-.14.06-.14.14v6.74c0 .08-.06.14-.14.14H8.04c-.08 0-.14-.06-.14-.14V8.5c0-.1-.08-.18-.18-.18H4.2c-.08 0-.14-.06-.14-.14V4.72c0-.08.06-.14.14-.14h11.6z" fill="#666"></path></svg><a target="_blank" class="eogvy9v0 css-1rbxkkv ef1hf1w0" href="/policies-and-standards" data-qa="BaseLink-renderAnchor-StyledAnchor">Why you can trust SCMP</a></div></div></div></div></div><div data-qa="GenericArticle-Correction" class="css-f4szbn eg5341w13"></div><div data-qa="GenericArticle-SpeechPlayer" class="css-xg4r6f eg5341w0"><div data-qa="ArticleSpeechInlineWidgetGeneric-Wrapper" class="css-fma335 egghhyv1"><div class="e1oct4f93 css-a5jxnj e9t53i10" data-qa="EmptyButton-Container"><div data-qa="EmptyButton-IconWrapper" class="css-1duflnb e9t53i12"><svg width="28" height="24" viewBox="0 0 28 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" data-qa="EmptyButton-StyledIcon" class="css-ozd7xs e9t53i11"><path d="M14 1C11.6131 1 9.32387 1.96119 7.63604 3.67211C5.94821 5.38304 5 7.70355 5 10.1232V17.0607C5.00017 17.575 5.20179 18.0681 5.56053 18.4318C5.91928 18.7955 6.4058 18.9998 6.91314 19H8.30043C8.80788 19 9.29457 18.7957 9.65345 18.432C10.0123 18.0683 10.214 17.5751 10.2142 17.0607V13.4948C10.2142 13.2401 10.1647 12.9879 10.0685 12.7525C9.97234 12.5172 9.83136 12.3034 9.65364 12.1233C9.47592 11.9432 9.26494 11.8004 9.03275 11.7029C8.80057 11.6055 8.55172 11.5554 8.30043 11.5555H7.22364V10.1219C7.22364 8.30006 7.93758 6.55288 9.20839 5.26468C10.4792 3.97648 12.2028 3.25277 14 3.25277C15.7972 3.25277 17.5208 3.97648 18.7916 5.26468C20.0624 6.55288 20.7764 8.30006 20.7764 10.1219V11.5555H19.6996C19.4483 11.5554 19.1994 11.6055 18.9672 11.7029C18.7351 11.8004 18.5241 11.9432 18.3464 12.1233C18.1686 12.3034 18.0277 12.5172 17.9315 12.7525C17.8353 12.9879 17.7858 13.2401 17.7858 13.4948V17.0607C17.786 17.5751 17.9877 18.0683 18.3465 18.432C18.7054 18.7957 19.1921 19 19.6996 19H21.0869C21.5942 18.9998 22.0807 18.7955 22.4395 18.4318C22.7982 18.0681 22.9998 17.575 23 17.0607V10.1232C23 8.92509 22.7672 7.73875 22.3149 6.63188C21.8626 5.52501 21.1997 4.51928 20.364 3.67211C19.5282 2.82495 18.5361 2.15294 17.4442 1.69446C16.3522 1.23598 15.1819 1 14 1Z" fill="white"></path></svg></div></div></div> </div><div data-qa="GenericArticle-Content" class="css-nxvtd4 eg5341w15"><section data-qa="ContentBody-ContentBodyContainer" class="e1oct4f97 css-19sk4h4 e1n4d2ln0"><div class="js-reading-0-percent-completion-tracker css-19icq8a e1gsc5vp0" data-qa="useTrackViewedPercentageRender-trackViewedPercentageRenders-TrackPercentageBlock"></div><p datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1c6uqr6 e1346ty31">For many students around the world, the illicit book-sharing website Library Genesis has been a lifeline of free primary texts and scientific knowledge.</p><div datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1xdhyk6 e1346ty30">It is such a widely accepted resource for free books that the Zhongnan University of Economics and Law posted a link to the site on its official Weibo account in July 2021, even as other users complained on the microblogging site about it being blocked by the <a class="euc41pk0 e13op9j60 e1qbu6wp1 css-jgjyn2 ef1hf1w0" href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/great-firewall?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" data-qa="BaseLink-renderAnchor-StyledAnchor"><span data-qa="Component-Text" class="css-0 e1qbu6wp0">Great Firewall</span></a>. A piece of Web3 technology called Interplanetary File System (IPFS), however, has been helping the book-sharing platform, often referred to as LibGen, bust through the firewall, allowing access to millions of books, including dozens of banned Chinese works.</div><p datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1c6uqr6 e1346ty31">After LibGen integrated IPFS in 2020, its massive collection of copyrighted books could suddenly be shared from any number of IP addresses and web domains, increasing the work of censors scouring the internet for areas that fall through the cracks. This is just one of the ways that Web3, the concept of a new version of the World Wide Web based on decentralisation and blockchain that is sometimes called Web 3.0, challenges government control, even as China seeks to play a leading role in these technologies.</p></section><section data-qa="ContentBody-ContentBodyContainer" class=" e1oct4f96 css-1myfomw e1n4d2ln0"><p datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1c6uqr6 e1346ty31">“Around 2016, many Chinese books uploaded on LibGen were not academic books, but books discussing political and public issues,” said a Chinese student pursuing a computer science master’s degree in Southeast Asia, who asked to go by James. He runs LibGen bot on his own server for Mastodon, a decentralised social media platform. “In particular, books from the Chinese University of Hong Kong and some Taiwanese publishing houses were scanned and uploaded in large numbers. I can’t remember when LibGen was blocked by the Great Firewall, but I’ve always used a VPN to access LibGen myself.”</p><div class="image-inline-container e1kkz63z0 css-1llrc1m ecv2zmr0" data-qa="Component-renderMap-StyledDiv"><div data-qa="Component-Container" class="css-bjn8wh e1xb2kle0"><figure class="image-inline caption e76tpiq0 e1xb2kle1 css-18ms6eb eope0cl0" data-qa="ArticleImage-ArticleImageContainer"><div data-qa="ArticleImage-ImageContainer" class="css-0 eope0cl3"><img data-qa="BaseImage-handleRenderImage-StyledImage" class="eope0cl2 css-3q8izr em4672x0" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.i-scmp.com/sites/default/files/d8/images/canvas/2022/03/30/b2e5b788-82ed-4c9d-8ac2-1d33d935cbcc_13be8470.jpg" title="Being widely spoken does not guarantee a language is well represented on Library Genesis, a Russia-based platform that consists mostly of English and Russian texts."/></div><figcaption data-qa="ArticleImage-DescriptionContainer" class="css-6potyr eope0cl1">Being widely spoken does not guarantee a language is well represented on Library Genesis, a Russia-based platform that consists mostly of English and Russian texts.</figcaption></figure></div></div><p datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1c6uqr6 e1346ty31">Research on LibGen usage in the early 2010s from Balázs Bodó, an associate professor on University of Amsterdam’s Faculty of Law who studies digital piracy and blockchain, shows that it has been largely used for the distribution of works on natural sciences and mathematics, but the collection of literature and social science texts has grown significantly over time.</p><div class="js-reading-20-percent-completion-tracker css-19icq8a e1gsc5vp0" data-qa="useTrackViewedPercentageRender-trackViewedPercentageRenders-TrackPercentageBlock"></div><p datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1c6uqr6 e1346ty31">One person on Weibo professed love for LibGen as a source of literature, showing search results for Chinese writer Li Yiyun, who teaches creative writing at Princeton University. “I will never buy [primary texts] again,” the person wrote.</p><p datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1c6uqr6 e1346ty31">As LibGen’s Chinese collection has grown, so too has the collection of political and banned works. A search of the database shows 65 works identified by <em data-qa="ContentSchemaRender-defaultRenderMapFunctions-Component-1" class="css-1mniedq eq9i94315">China Digital Times</em> as banned or previously banned for publication in China are available for download. Several other books touching on sensitive subjects that cannot be found for sale in China are also on the platform.</p><p datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1c6uqr6 e1346ty31">The banned works, freely available to download over IPFS, include those by Nobel laureates, political dissidents, foreign writers, and even Communist Party cadres. Some of the works appear to still be sold online in some form, such as <em data-qa="ContentSchemaRender-defaultRenderMapFunctions-Component-1" class="css-1mniedq eq9i94315">Jin Ping Mei</em>, a celebrated 17th Century novel criticised as pornographic in China and banned by the Qing dynasty and the Communist Party. It has gained a reputation similar to that of Vladimir Nabokov’s <em data-qa="ContentSchemaRender-defaultRenderMapFunctions-Component-3" class="css-1mniedq eq9i94315">Lolita</em>, Chinese translations of which are also available on LibGen.</p><div data-qa="Component-Container" class=" css-1jyke50 e1cwk53e0"></div><p datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1c6uqr6 e1346ty31">Other works available are strictly banned in China, turning up no results on e-commerce sites like Taobao and Dangdang. These include <em data-qa="ContentSchemaRender-defaultRenderMapFunctions-Component-1" class="css-1mniedq eq9i94315">China in Ten Words</em> by Yu Hua, <em data-qa="ContentSchemaRender-defaultRenderMapFunctions-Component-3" class="css-1mniedq eq9i94315">A Single Blade and Toxic Sword: Critique on Contemporary Chinese Nationalism</em> by Nobel Peace Prize winner Liu Xiaobo, <em data-qa="ContentSchemaRender-defaultRenderMapFunctions-Component-5" class="css-1mniedq eq9i94315">Tombstone: The Great Chinese Famine</em> by Yang Jisheng, and <em data-qa="ContentSchemaRender-defaultRenderMapFunctions-Component-7" class="css-1mniedq eq9i94315">The Private Life of Chairman Mao</em>, a memoir by Mao Zedong’s personal doctor Li Zhisui, which offers an unflattering look at the founder of the People’s Republic of China.</p><h3 type="h3" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e14khtrb0 css-17x7qa9 e793b7w1"><a class="link-text css-e0dnmk ef1hf1w0" href="https://www.scmp.com/abacus/tech/article/3096044/google-using-tool-chinese-users-developed-bypass-great-firewall?module=hard_link&amp;pgtype=article" style="inline-size:100%" data-qa="BaseLink-renderAnchor-StyledAnchor"><div data-qa="DigitalArchiveLink-RootContainer" class=" css-iqvku8 eeeqn936"><div data-qa="DigitalArchiveLink-LeftContainer" class="css-1q3ym6v eeeqn935"><div data-qa="DigitalArchiveLink-TitleContainer" class="css-pcbgty eeeqn931"><span data-qa="DigitalArchiveLink-TitleText" class="css-66qo9a eeeqn932">Google is using a tool Chinese users developed to bypass the Great Firewall</span></div><div data-qa="DigitalArchiveLink-UpdatedDateContainer" class="css-1jao69x eeeqn930"></div></div><div data-qa="DigitalArchiveLink-RightContainer" class="css-0 eeeqn934"><div data-qa="DigitalArchiveLink-ImageContainer" class="css-12nlsj4 eeeqn933"></div></div></div></a></h3><p datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1c6uqr6 e1346ty31">The availability of these books gave censors a reason to ban the site, but it does not necessarily mean people are downloading them. Social media posts show that many people simply want to download books assigned at university for free, and LibGen has traditionally been associated with scientific knowledge.</p><div class="js-reading-50-percent-completion-tracker css-19icq8a e1gsc5vp0" data-qa="useTrackViewedPercentageRender-trackViewedPercentageRenders-TrackPercentageBlock"></div><p datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1c6uqr6 e1346ty31">“One way to explain [the growth in usage] is that China is making its mark in the global knowledge economy and has world-class universities, where they are engaging much more deeply with the Western scientific canon, of which Library Genesis is still the most important source,” Bodó said.</p><p datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1c6uqr6 e1346ty31">No matter which books people are trying to share, the integration of IPFS has made it easier than ever to do so without the use of a virtual private network (VPN) to get around the firewall.</p><p datatype="p" data-qa="Component-Component" class="e15kmbpe0 css-1c6uqr6 e1346ty31"><strong data-qa="ContentSchemaRender-defaultRenderMapFunctions-Component-0" class="css-1mniedq eq9i94316">12 other banned political works on LibGen</strong></p><div class="scmp-code-block methode-html-wrapper e1kkz63z0 css-1llrc1m ecv2zmr0" data-qa="Component-renderMap-StyledDiv">
<div data-qa="Component-StyledContainer" class="css-17hddwn ekzbjai3"><div data-qa="Component-Caption" class="css-2fq7y3 ekzbjai4"></div><div data-qa="Component-TableContainer" class="css-ofw23y ekzbjai2"><table data-qa="Component-StyledTable" class="css-1q3ym6v ekzbjai1">
